        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 5:13PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Centenary, or 13 miles south of Charlottesville,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Frequent cloud to ground lightning
strikes.

Locations impacted include...
Palmyra, Lake Monticello, Ferncliff, Kents Store, Troy, Scottsville,
Nahor, Zion Crossroads, Central Plains, Antioch, Union Mills,
Wildwood, Bybee, Wilmington, and Cunningham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
